{"TopicId":176823,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Making a custom flag, help","CreatedByName":"QvestionAnswerNeeded","CreatedById":190187,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T08:33:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"QvestionAnswerNeeded","CreatedById":190187,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T08:33:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would be a good program for making an image? I\u2019m trying to make a custom flag for my planes, and I know how to get the flag into KSP, but I can\u2019t find a program that can make an image. I don\u2019t really want to get an app... plz help\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T15:15:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223417510\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531902834\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190187\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022QvestionAnswerNeeded\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, QvestionAnswerNeeded said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would be a good program for making an image? I\u2019m trying to make a custom flag for my planes, and I know how to get the flag into KSP, but I can\u2019t find a program that can make an image. I don\u2019t really want to get an app... plz help\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPhotoshop or Gimp. Even MS paint will do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T15:20:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.getpaint.net/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.getpaint.net/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou don\u0027t really need much more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vexillar","CreatedById":178802,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T15:21:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223417683\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531926945\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPhotoshop or Gimp. Even MS paint will do.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis, exactly.\u00A0 Anything that will save a 256 x 160 pixel image in .png format.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-18T15:22:21Z\u0022 title=\u002207/18/2018 03:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 18, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Vexillar\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T16:21:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also use Microsoft Publisher, or any of the photo-editing software, even opensource stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you\u0027d like some help, tell me what you\u0027re looking for and I will see what I can come up with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-18T22:05:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used MSPaint.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s a tip for you, though. To avoid problems with sizing and format, open a stock flag in your editing software, blank it, and put your own image in the space. And then of course save it under a different name.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"QvestionAnswerNeeded","CreatedById":190187,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-19T15:48:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThx all of you, found what I was looking for\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThink I\u2019ll use FireAlpaca\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-21T17:42:35Z\u0022 title=\u002207/21/2018 05:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by QvestionAnswerNeeded\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAnother thought\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}